# Keep secrets + non-runtime artifacts out of ANY Vercel upload (defense-in-depth, esp. for a
# CLI / local-dir deploy where untracked files could otherwise ride along). `next build` only
# bundles what app/ + lib/ import, so none of these are needed at runtime.
# SECRETS — never upload:
.env
.env*.local
# Python v1 prototype + its generated artifacts (carry legacy "DoorDash" strings; the differential
# oracle reads them at TEST time only, never at build/runtime):
out/
scripts/
*.csv
RULES_CONFIG_DUMP.txt
# Dev-only tooling / generators / docs not needed by the deployed app:
scripts-ts/
reference/
.agents/
# NOTE: lib/ (incl. lib/data/*.snapshot.json) + app/ + components/ are REQUIRED by the build — not ignored.
